<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Before I woke up, this strange calm and silent darkness that engulfed me in its grasp. It held me there for what seemed like an eternity without really holding me at all. I was completely naïve I didn’t know what was out there in the world around me, but then it happened.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I was suddenly ripped out of that place that had imprisoned me. Torn backwards through what seemed like a snaking tunnel of flashing lights and energy. Then there was a massive burst of light all around me. I was snapped back to a place I did not know the blistering cold lashing out at every part of my body. I was lying flat on my stomach against the snow-covered ground as wind whipped over my back. I gasp for air as I force myself onto my hands and knees, my whole body was trembling. That’s when I realized lying in a puddle of dark red blood, I could tell it was mine by my soaked clothing. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I must have been lying there for hours, my body was so cold I couldn’t feel a wound. As I stirred I managed to get a look at what was around me. It was a village set a flame, bodies that looked like me a moment ago dead in the crimson snow. The buildings where engulfed with dancing flames. I looked at the burning house nearest to me, I could feel the warmth and yearned to be closer to it. I moved my hand to rush forward towards the fire, my hand touched something warm in the snow. Anything warm was instantly valuable to me as I snatched it up as I crawled. I didn’t even examine what I had found until I was within the warm of the fire.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I thrust my hands towards the fire instinctively as I felt the cold recede from my fingers. Only then did I pause to feel my back where my wound should have been. I only felt my bare skin and the slit in my clothing, the frozen blood on my clothes was misleading me, or was it? Confused I looked down at the object I had found in the snow. It was a large sword how it managed to stay warm in the snow, I do not know. I remember this was the first time I traced my fingers over the Runes. My mind began to blur at this exact moment. I had dozens of thought blurring through my mind! Where am I? Is this my village? What Happened? Who am I?<br>
<br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp …The Beginning…<br>
